                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            <p>Fragment. Dated to the year 40 something of a Cōḻa king whose name is lost. This is Kulottuṅga I Cōḻa (r. 1070-1120) according to <bibl><ptr target="bib:Vijayavenugopal+al2026_01"/></bibl>, who, indeed, is the only Cōḻa king to have reigned for more than 40 years.</p>
                            <p>On a block in the north wall of the <foreign>mahāmaṇḍapa</foreign>.</p>
                        </summary>
                        
                    </msContents>
